32// Transport header size in bytes. Assume UDP/IPv4 as a reasonable minimum.
33constexpr size_t kTransportOverhead = 28;
34
35constexpr uint16_t kOldSequenceThreshold = 0x3fff;
36} // namespace

38ForwardErrorCorrection::Packet::Packet() : data(0), ref_count_(0) {}
39ForwardErrorCorrection::Packet::~Packet() = default;
40
41int32_t ForwardErrorCorrection::Packet::AddRef() {
42 return ++ref_count_;
43}
44
45int32_t ForwardErrorCorrection::Packet::Release() {
46 int32_t ref_count;
47 ref_count = --ref_count_;
48 if (ref_count == 0)
49 delete this;
50 return ref_count;
51}

53// This comparator is used to compare std::unique_ptr's pointing to
54// subclasses of SortablePackets. It needs to be parametric since
55// the std::unique_ptr's are not covariant w.r.t. the types that
56// they are pointing to.
57template <typename S, typename T>
58bool ForwardErrorCorrection::SortablePacket::LessThan::operator()(
59 const S& first,
60 const T& second) {
61 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(first->ssrc, second->ssrc);
62 return IsNewerSequenceNumber(second->seq_num, first->seq_num);
63}

77ForwardErrorCorrection::ForwardErrorCorrection(
78 std::unique_ptr<FecHeaderReader> fec_header_reader,
79 std::unique_ptr<FecHeaderWriter> fec_header_writer,
80 uint32_t ssrc,
81 uint32_t protected_media_ssrc)
82 : ssrc_(ssrc),
83 protected_media_ssrc_(protected_media_ssrc),
84 fec_header_reader_(std::move(fec_header_reader)),
85 fec_header_writer_(std::move(fec_header_writer)),
86 generated_fec_packets_(fec_header_writer_->MaxFecPackets()),
87 packet_mask_size_(0) {}

91std::unique_ptr<ForwardErrorCorrection> ForwardErrorCorrection::CreateUlpfec(
92 uint32_t ssrc) {
93 std::unique_ptr<FecHeaderReader> fec_header_reader(new UlpfecHeaderReader());
94 std::unique_ptr<FecHeaderWriter> fec_header_writer(new UlpfecHeaderWriter());
95 return std::unique_ptr<ForwardErrorCorrection>(new ForwardErrorCorrection(
96 std::move(fec_header_reader), std::move(fec_header_writer), ssrc, ssrc));

101 uint32_t protected_media_ssrc) {
102 std::unique_ptr<FecHeaderReader> fec_header_reader(new FlexfecHeaderReader());
103 std::unique_ptr<FecHeaderWriter> fec_header_writer(new FlexfecHeaderWriter());

105 std::move(fec_header_reader), std::move(fec_header_writer), ssrc,
106 protected_media_ssrc));

109int ForwardErrorCorrection::EncodeFec(const PacketList& media_packets,
110 uint8_t protection_factor,
111 int num_important_packets,
112 bool use_unequal_protection,
113 FecMaskType fec_mask_type,
114 std::list<Packet*>* fec_packets) {
115 const size_t num_media_packets = media_packets.size();
116
117 // Sanity check arguments.
118 RTC_DCHECK_GT(num_media_packets, 0);
119 RTC_DCHECK_GE(num_important_packets, 0);
120 RTC_DCHECK_LE(num_important_packets, num_media_packets);
121 RTC_DCHECK(fec_packets->empty());
122 const size_t max_media_packets = fec_header_writer_->MaxMediaPackets();
123 if (num_media_packets > max_media_packets) {
124 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Can't protect " << num_media_packets
125 << " media packets per frame. Max is "
126 << max_media_packets << ".";
127 return -1;
128 }
129
130 // Error check the media packets.
131 for (const auto& media_packet : media_packets) {
132 RTC_DCHECK(media_packet);
133 if (media_packet->data.size() < kRtpHeaderSize) {
134 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Media packet " << media_packet->data.size()
135 << " bytes "
136 "is smaller than RTP header.";
137 return -1;
138 }
139 // Ensure the FEC packets will fit in a typical MTU.
140 if (media_packet->data.size() + MaxPacketOverhead() + kTransportOverhead >
141 IP_PACKET_SIZE) {
142 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Media packet " << media_packet->data.size()
143 << " bytes "
144 "with overhead is larger than "
145 << IP_PACKET_SIZE << " bytes.";
146 }
147 }
148
149 // Prepare generated FEC packets.
150 int num_fec_packets = NumFecPackets(num_media_packets, protection_factor);
151 if (num_fec_packets == 0) {
152 return 0;
153 }
154 for (int i = 0; i < num_fec_packets; ++i) {
155 generated_fec_packets_[i].data.EnsureCapacity(IP_PACKET_SIZE);
156 memset(generated_fec_packets_[i].data.MutableData(), 0, IP_PACKET_SIZE);
157 // Use this as a marker for untouched packets.
158 generated_fec_packets_[i].data.SetSize(0);
159 fec_packets->push_back(&generated_fec_packets_[i]);
160 }
161
162 internal::PacketMaskTable mask_table(fec_mask_type, num_media_packets);
163 packet_mask_size_ = internal::PacketMaskSize(num_media_packets);
164 memset(packet_masks_, 0, num_fec_packets * packet_mask_size_);
165 internal::GeneratePacketMasks(num_media_packets, num_fec_packets,
166 num_important_packets, use_unequal_protection,
167 &mask_table, packet_masks_);
168
169 // Adapt packet masks to missing media packets.
170 int num_mask_bits = InsertZerosInPacketMasks(media_packets, num_fec_packets);
171 if (num_mask_bits < 0) {
172 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Due to sequence number gaps, cannot protect media "
173 "packets with a single block of FEC packets.";
174 fec_packets->clear();
175 return -1;
176 }
177 packet_mask_size_ = internal::PacketMaskSize(num_mask_bits);
178
179 // Write FEC packets to |generated_fec_packets_|.
180 GenerateFecPayloads(media_packets, num_fec_packets);
181 // TODO(brandtr): Generalize this when multistream protection support is
182 // added.
183 const uint32_t media_ssrc = ParseSsrc(media_packets.front()->data.data());
184 const uint16_t seq_num_base =
185 ParseSequenceNumber(media_packets.front()->data.data());
186 FinalizeFecHeaders(num_fec_packets, media_ssrc, seq_num_base);
187
188 return 0;
189}
190
191int ForwardErrorCorrection::NumFecPackets(int num_media_packets,
192 int protection_factor) {
193 // Result in Q0 with an unsigned round.
194 int num_fec_packets = (num_media_packets * protection_factor + (1 << 7)) >> 8;
195 // Generate at least one FEC packet if we need protection.
196 if (protection_factor > 0 && num_fec_packets == 0) {
197 num_fec_packets = 1;
198 }
199 RTC_DCHECK_LE(num_fec_packets, num_media_packets);
200 return num_fec_packets;
201}
202
203void ForwardErrorCorrection::GenerateFecPayloads(
204 const PacketList& media_packets,
205 size_t num_fec_packets) {
206 RTC_DCHECK(!media_packets.empty());
207 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_fec_packets; ++i) {
208 Packet* const fec_packet = &generated_fec_packets_[i];
209 size_t pkt_mask_idx = i * packet_mask_size_;
210 const size_t min_packet_mask_size = fec_header_writer_->MinPacketMaskSize(
211 &packet_masks_[pkt_mask_idx], packet_mask_size_);
212 const size_t fec_header_size =
213 fec_header_writer_->FecHeaderSize(min_packet_mask_size);
214
215 size_t media_pkt_idx = 0;
216 auto media_packets_it = media_packets.cbegin();
217 uint16_t prev_seq_num =
218 ParseSequenceNumber((*media_packets_it)->data.data());
219 while (media_packets_it != media_packets.end()) {
220 Packet* const media_packet = media_packets_it->get();
221 const uint8_t* media_packet_data = media_packet->data.cdata();
222 // Should |media_packet| be protected by |fec_packet|?
223 if (packet_masks_[pkt_mask_idx] & (1 << (7 - media_pkt_idx))) {
224 size_t media_payload_length =
225 media_packet->data.size() - kRtpHeaderSize;
226
227 bool first_protected_packet = (fec_packet->data.size() == 0);
228 size_t fec_packet_length = fec_header_size + media_payload_length;
229 if (fec_packet_length > fec_packet->data.size()) {
230 // Recall that XORing with zero (which the FEC packets are prefilled
231 // with) is the identity operator, thus all prior XORs are
232 // still correct even though we expand the packet length here.
233 fec_packet->data.SetSize(fec_packet_length);
234 }
235 if (first_protected_packet) {
236 uint8_t* data = fec_packet->data.MutableData();
237 // Write P, X, CC, M, and PT recovery fields.
238 // Note that bits 0, 1, and 16 are overwritten in FinalizeFecHeaders.
239 memcpy(&data[0], &media_packet_data[0], 2);
240 // Write length recovery field. (This is a temporary location for
241 // ULPFEC.)
242 ByteWriter<uint16_t>::WriteBigEndian(&data[2], media_payload_length);
243 // Write timestamp recovery field.
244 memcpy(&data[4], &media_packet_data[4], 4);
245 // Write payload.
246 if (media_payload_length > 0) {
247 memcpy(&data[fec_header_size], &media_packet_data[kRtpHeaderSize],
248 media_payload_length);
249 }
250 } else {
251 XorHeaders(*media_packet, fec_packet);
252 XorPayloads(*media_packet, media_payload_length, fec_header_size,
253 fec_packet);
254 }
255 }
256 media_packets_it++;
257 if (media_packets_it != media_packets.end()) {
258 uint16_t seq_num =
259 ParseSequenceNumber((*media_packets_it)->data.data());
260 media_pkt_idx += static_cast<uint16_t>(seq_num - prev_seq_num);
261 prev_seq_num = seq_num;
262 }
263 pkt_mask_idx += media_pkt_idx / 8;
264 media_pkt_idx %= 8;
265 }
266 RTC_DCHECK_GT(fec_packet->data.size(), 0)
267 << "Packet mask is wrong or poorly designed.";
268 }
269}
270
271int ForwardErrorCorrection::InsertZerosInPacketMasks(
272 const PacketList& media_packets,
273 size_t num_fec_packets) {
274 size_t num_media_packets = media_packets.size();
275 if (num_media_packets <= 1) {
276 return num_media_packets;
277 }
278 uint16_t last_seq_num =
279 ParseSequenceNumber(media_packets.back()->data.data());
280 uint16_t first_seq_num =
281 ParseSequenceNumber(media_packets.front()->data.data());
282 size_t total_missing_seq_nums =
283 static_cast<uint16_t>(last_seq_num - first_seq_num) - num_media_packets +
284 1;
285 if (total_missing_seq_nums == 0) {
286 // All sequence numbers are covered by the packet mask.
287 // No zero insertion required.
288 return num_media_packets;
289 }
290 const size_t max_media_packets = fec_header_writer_->MaxMediaPackets();
291 if (total_missing_seq_nums + num_media_packets > max_media_packets) {
292 return -1;
293 }
294 // Allocate the new mask.
295 size_t tmp_packet_mask_size =
296 internal::PacketMaskSize(total_missing_seq_nums + num_media_packets);
297 memset(tmp_packet_masks_, 0, num_fec_packets * tmp_packet_mask_size);
298
299 auto media_packets_it = media_packets.cbegin();
300 uint16_t prev_seq_num = first_seq_num;
301 ++media_packets_it;
302
303 // Insert the first column.
304 internal::CopyColumn(tmp_packet_masks_, tmp_packet_mask_size, packet_masks_,
305 packet_mask_size_, num_fec_packets, 0, 0);
306 size_t new_bit_index = 1;
307 size_t old_bit_index = 1;
308 // Insert zeros in the bit mask for every hole in the sequence.
309 while (media_packets_it != media_packets.end()) {
310 if (new_bit_index == max_media_packets) {
311 // We can only cover up to 48 packets.
312 break;
313 }
314 uint16_t seq_num = ParseSequenceNumber((*media_packets_it)->data.data());
315 const int num_zeros_to_insert =
316 static_cast<uint16_t>(seq_num - prev_seq_num - 1);
317 if (num_zeros_to_insert > 0) {
318 internal::InsertZeroColumns(num_zeros_to_insert, tmp_packet_masks_,
319 tmp_packet_mask_size, num_fec_packets,
320 new_bit_index);
321 }
322 new_bit_index += num_zeros_to_insert;
323 internal::CopyColumn(tmp_packet_masks_, tmp_packet_mask_size, packet_masks_,
324 packet_mask_size_, num_fec_packets, new_bit_index,
325 old_bit_index);
326 ++new_bit_index;
327 ++old_bit_index;
328 prev_seq_num = seq_num;
329 ++media_packets_it;
330 }
331 if (new_bit_index % 8 != 0) {
332 // We didn't fill the last byte. Shift bits to correct position.
333 for (uint16_t row = 0; row < num_fec_packets; ++row) {
334 int new_byte_index = row * tmp_packet_mask_size + new_bit_index / 8;
335 tmp_packet_masks_[new_byte_index] <<= (7 - (new_bit_index % 8));
336 }
337 }
338 // Replace the old mask with the new.
339 memcpy(packet_masks_, tmp_packet_masks_,
340 num_fec_packets * tmp_packet_mask_size);
341 return new_bit_index;
342}
343
344void ForwardErrorCorrection::FinalizeFecHeaders(size_t num_fec_packets,
345 uint32_t media_ssrc,
346 uint16_t seq_num_base) {
347 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_fec_packets; ++i) {
348 fec_header_writer_->FinalizeFecHeader(
349 media_ssrc, seq_num_base, &packet_masks_[i * packet_mask_size_],
350 packet_mask_size_, &generated_fec_packets_[i]);
351 }
352}

354void ForwardErrorCorrection::ResetState(
355 RecoveredPacketList* recovered_packets) {
356 // Free the memory for any existing recovered packets, if the caller hasn't.
357 recovered_packets->clear();
358 received_fec_packets_.clear();
359}
360
361void ForwardErrorCorrection::InsertMediaPacket(
362 RecoveredPacketList* recovered_packets,
363 const ReceivedPacket& received_packet) {
364 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(received_packet.ssrc, protected_media_ssrc_);
365
366 // Search for duplicate packets.
367 for (const auto& recovered_packet : *recovered_packets) {
368 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(recovered_packet->ssrc, received_packet.ssrc);
369 if (recovered_packet->seq_num == received_packet.seq_num) {
370 // Duplicate packet, no need to add to list.
371 return;
372 }
373 }
374
375 std::unique_ptr<RecoveredPacket> recovered_packet(new RecoveredPacket());
376 // This "recovered packet" was not recovered using parity packets.
377 recovered_packet->was_recovered = false;
378 // This media packet has already been passed on.
379 recovered_packet->returned = true;
380 recovered_packet->ssrc = received_packet.ssrc;
381 recovered_packet->seq_num = received_packet.seq_num;
382 recovered_packet->pkt = received_packet.pkt;
383 // TODO(holmer): Consider replacing this with a binary search for the right
384 // position, and then just insert the new packet. Would get rid of the sort.
385 RecoveredPacket* recovered_packet_ptr = recovered_packet.get();
386 recovered_packets->push_back(std::move(recovered_packet));
387 recovered_packets->sort(SortablePacket::LessThan());
388 UpdateCoveringFecPackets(*recovered_packet_ptr);
389}
390
391void ForwardErrorCorrection::UpdateCoveringFecPackets(
392 const RecoveredPacket& packet) {
393 for (auto& fec_packet : received_fec_packets_) {
394 // Is this FEC packet protecting the media packet |packet|?
395 auto protected_it = absl::c_lower_bound(
396 fec_packet->protected_packets, &packet, SortablePacket::LessThan());
397 if (protected_it != fec_packet->protected_packets.end() &&
398 (*protected_it)->seq_num == packet.seq_num) {
399 // Found an FEC packet which is protecting |packet|.
400 (*protected_it)->pkt = packet.pkt;
401 }
402 }
403}
404
405void ForwardErrorCorrection::InsertFecPacket(
406 const RecoveredPacketList& recovered_packets,
407 const ReceivedPacket& received_packet) {
408 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(received_packet.ssrc, ssrc_);
409
410 // Check for duplicate.
411 for (const auto& existing_fec_packet : received_fec_packets_) {
412 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(existing_fec_packet->ssrc, received_packet.ssrc);
413 if (existing_fec_packet->seq_num == received_packet.seq_num) {
414 // Drop duplicate FEC packet data.
415 return;
416 }
417 }
418
419 std::unique_ptr<ReceivedFecPacket> fec_packet(new ReceivedFecPacket());
420 fec_packet->pkt = received_packet.pkt;
421 fec_packet->ssrc = received_packet.ssrc;
422 fec_packet->seq_num = received_packet.seq_num;
423 // Parse ULPFEC/FlexFEC header specific info.
424 bool ret = fec_header_reader_->ReadFecHeader(fec_packet.get());
425 if (!ret) {
426 return;
427 }
428
429 // TODO(brandtr): Update here when we support multistream protection.
430 if (fec_packet->protected_ssrc != protected_media_ssrc_) {
431 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
432 << "Received FEC packet is protecting an unknown media SSRC; dropping.";
433 return;
434 }
435
436 if (fec_packet->packet_mask_offset + fec_packet->packet_mask_size >
437 fec_packet->pkt->data.size()) {
438 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Received corrupted FEC packet; dropping.";
439 return;
440 }
441
442 // Parse packet mask from header and represent as protected packets.
443 for (uint16_t byte_idx = 0; byte_idx < fec_packet->packet_mask_size;
444 ++byte_idx) {
445 uint8_t packet_mask =
446 fec_packet->pkt->data[fec_packet->packet_mask_offset + byte_idx];
447 for (uint16_t bit_idx = 0; bit_idx < 8; ++bit_idx) {
448 if (packet_mask & (1 << (7 - bit_idx))) {
449 std::unique_ptr<ProtectedPacket> protected_packet(
450 new ProtectedPacket());
451 // This wraps naturally with the sequence number.
452 protected_packet->ssrc = protected_media_ssrc_;
453 protected_packet->seq_num = static_cast<uint16_t>(
454 fec_packet->seq_num_base + (byte_idx << 3) + bit_idx);
455 protected_packet->pkt = nullptr;
456 fec_packet->protected_packets.push_back(std::move(protected_packet));
457 }
458 }
459 }
460
461 if (fec_packet->protected_packets.empty()) {
462 // All-zero packet mask; we can discard this FEC packet.
463 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Received FEC packet has an all-zero packet mask.";
464 } else {
465 AssignRecoveredPackets(recovered_packets, fec_packet.get());
466 // TODO(holmer): Consider replacing this with a binary search for the right
467 // position, and then just insert the new packet. Would get rid of the sort.
468 received_fec_packets_.push_back(std::move(fec_packet));
469 received_fec_packets_.sort(SortablePacket::LessThan());
470 const size_t max_fec_packets = fec_header_reader_->MaxFecPackets();
471 if (received_fec_packets_.size() > max_fec_packets) {
472 received_fec_packets_.pop_front();
473 }
474 RTC_DCHECK_LE(received_fec_packets_.size(), max_fec_packets);
475 }
476}
477
478void ForwardErrorCorrection::AssignRecoveredPackets(
479 const RecoveredPacketList& recovered_packets,
480 ReceivedFecPacket* fec_packet) {
481 ProtectedPacketList* protected_packets = &fec_packet->protected_packets;
482 std::vector<RecoveredPacket*> recovered_protected_packets;
483
484 // Find intersection between the (sorted) containers |protected_packets|
485 // and |recovered_packets|, i.e. all protected packets that have already
486 // been recovered. Update the corresponding protected packets to point to
487 // the recovered packets.
488 auto it_p = protected_packets->cbegin();
489 auto it_r = recovered_packets.cbegin();
490 SortablePacket::LessThan less_than;
491 while (it_p != protected_packets->end() && it_r != recovered_packets.end()) {
492 if (less_than(*it_p, *it_r)) {
493 ++it_p;
494 } else if (less_than(*it_r, *it_p)) {
495 ++it_r;
496 } else { // *it_p == *it_r.
497 // This protected packet has already been recovered.
498 (*it_p)->pkt = (*it_r)->pkt;
499 ++it_p;
500 ++it_r;
501 }
502 }
503}
504
505void ForwardErrorCorrection::InsertPacket(
506 const ReceivedPacket& received_packet,
507 RecoveredPacketList* recovered_packets) {
508 // Discard old FEC packets such that the sequence numbers in
509 // |received_fec_packets_| span at most 1/2 of the sequence number space.
510 // This is important for keeping |received_fec_packets_| sorted, and may
511 // also reduce the possibility of incorrect decoding due to sequence number
512 // wrap-around.
513 if (!received_fec_packets_.empty() &&
514 received_packet.ssrc == received_fec_packets_.front()->ssrc) {
515 // It only makes sense to detect wrap-around when |received_packet|
516 // and |front_received_fec_packet| belong to the same sequence number
517 // space, i.e., the same SSRC. This happens when |received_packet|
518 // is a FEC packet, or if |received_packet| is a media packet and
519 // RED+ULPFEC is used.
520 auto it = received_fec_packets_.begin();
521 while (it != received_fec_packets_.end()) {
522 uint16_t seq_num_diff = MinDiff(received_packet.seq_num, (*it)->seq_num);
523 if (seq_num_diff > kOldSequenceThreshold) {
524 it = received_fec_packets_.erase(it);
525 } else {
526 // No need to keep iterating, since |received_fec_packets_| is sorted.
527 break;
528 }
529 }
530 }
531
532 if (received_packet.is_fec) {
533 InsertFecPacket(*recovered_packets, received_packet);
534 } else {
535 InsertMediaPacket(recovered_packets, received_packet);
536 }
537
538 DiscardOldRecoveredPackets(recovered_packets);
539}
540
541bool ForwardErrorCorrection::StartPacketRecovery(
542 const ReceivedFecPacket& fec_packet,
543 RecoveredPacket* recovered_packet) {
544 // Ensure pkt is initialized.
545 recovered_packet->pkt = new Packet();
546 // Sanity check packet length.
547 if (fec_packet.pkt->data.size() <
548 fec_packet.fec_header_size + fec_packet.protection_length) {
549 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
550 << "The FEC packet is truncated: it does not contain enough room "
551 "for its own header.";
552 return false;
553 }
554 if (fec_packet.protection_length >
555 std::min(size_t{IP_PACKET_SIZE - kRtpHeaderSize},
556 IP_PACKET_SIZE - fec_packet.fec_header_size)) {
557 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Incorrect protection length, dropping FEC packet.";
558 return false;
559 }
560 // Initialize recovered packet data.
561 recovered_packet->pkt->data.EnsureCapacity(IP_PACKET_SIZE);
562 recovered_packet->pkt->data.SetSize(fec_packet.protection_length +
563 kRtpHeaderSize);
564 recovered_packet->returned = false;
565 recovered_packet->was_recovered = true;
566 // Copy bytes corresponding to minimum RTP header size.
567 // Note that the sequence number and SSRC fields will be overwritten
568 // at the end of packet recovery.
569 memcpy(recovered_packet->pkt->data.MutableData(),
570 fec_packet.pkt->data.cdata(), kRtpHeaderSize);
571 // Copy remaining FEC payload.
572 if (fec_packet.protection_length > 0) {
573 memcpy(recovered_packet->pkt->data.MutableData() + kRtpHeaderSize,
574 fec_packet.pkt->data.cdata() + fec_packet.fec_header_size,
575 fec_packet.protection_length);
576 }
577 return true;
578}
579
580bool ForwardErrorCorrection::FinishPacketRecovery(
581 const ReceivedFecPacket& fec_packet,
582 RecoveredPacket* recovered_packet) {
583 uint8_t* data = recovered_packet->pkt->data.MutableData();
584 // Set the RTP version to 2.
585 data[0] |= 0x80; // Set the 1st bit.
586 data[0] &= 0xbf; // Clear the 2nd bit.
587 // Recover the packet length, from temporary location.
588 const size_t new_size =
589 ByteReader<uint16_t>::ReadBigEndian(&data[2]) + kRtpHeaderSize;
590 if (new_size > size_t{IP_PACKET_SIZE - kRtpHeaderSize}) {
591 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "The recovered packet had a length larger than a "
592 "typical IP packet, and is thus dropped.";
593 return false;
594 }
595 recovered_packet->pkt->data.SetSize(new_size);
596 // Set the SN field.
597 ByteWriter<uint16_t>::WriteBigEndian(&data[2], recovered_packet->seq_num);
598 // Set the SSRC field.
599 ByteWriter<uint32_t>::WriteBigEndian(&data[8], fec_packet.protected_ssrc);
600 recovered_packet->ssrc = fec_packet.protected_ssrc;
601 return true;
602}
603
604void ForwardErrorCorrection::XorHeaders(const Packet& src, Packet* dst) {
605 uint8_t* dst_data = dst->data.MutableData();
606 const uint8_t* src_data = src.data.cdata();
607 // XOR the first 2 bytes of the header: V, P, X, CC, M, PT fields.
608 dst_data[0] ^= src_data[0];
609 dst_data[1] ^= src_data[1];
610
611 // XOR the length recovery field.
612 uint8_t src_payload_length_network_order[2];
613 ByteWriter<uint16_t>::WriteBigEndian(src_payload_length_network_order,
614 src.data.size() - kRtpHeaderSize);
615 dst_data[2] ^= src_payload_length_network_order[0];
616 dst_data[3] ^= src_payload_length_network_order[1];
617
618 // XOR the 5th to 8th bytes of the header: the timestamp field.
619 dst_data[4] ^= src_data[4];
620 dst_data[5] ^= src_data[5];
621 dst_data[6] ^= src_data[6];
622 dst_data[7] ^= src_data[7];
623
624 // Skip the 9th to 12th bytes of the header.
625}
626
627void ForwardErrorCorrection::XorPayloads(const Packet& src,
628 size_t payload_length,
629 size_t dst_offset,
630 Packet* dst) {
631 // XOR the payload.
632 RTC_DCHECK_LE(kRtpHeaderSize + payload_length, src.data.size());
633 RTC_DCHECK_LE(dst_offset + payload_length, dst->data.capacity());
634 if (dst_offset + payload_length > dst->data.size()) {
635 dst->data.SetSize(dst_offset + payload_length);
636 }
637 uint8_t* dst_data = dst->data.MutableData();
638 const uint8_t* src_data = src.data.cdata();
639 for (size_t i = 0; i < payload_length; ++i) {
640 dst_data[dst_offset + i] ^= src_data[kRtpHeaderSize + i];
641 }
642}
643
644bool ForwardErrorCorrection::RecoverPacket(const ReceivedFecPacket& fec_packet,
645 RecoveredPacket* recovered_packet) {
646 if (!StartPacketRecovery(fec_packet, recovered_packet)) {
647 return false;
648 }
649 for (const auto& protected_packet : fec_packet.protected_packets) {
650 if (protected_packet->pkt == nullptr) {
651 // This is the packet we're recovering.
652 recovered_packet->seq_num = protected_packet->seq_num;
653 } else {
654 XorHeaders(*protected_packet->pkt, recovered_packet->pkt);
655 XorPayloads(*protected_packet->pkt,
656 protected_packet->pkt->data.size() - kRtpHeaderSize,
657 kRtpHeaderSize, recovered_packet->pkt);
658 }
659 }
660 if (!FinishPacketRecovery(fec_packet, recovered_packet)) {
661 return false;
662 }
663 return true;
664}
665
666void ForwardErrorCorrection::AttemptRecovery(
667 RecoveredPacketList* recovered_packets) {
668 auto fec_packet_it = received_fec_packets_.begin();
669 while (fec_packet_it != received_fec_packets_.end()) {
670 // Search for each FEC packet's protected media packets.
671 int packets_missing = NumCoveredPacketsMissing(**fec_packet_it);
672
673 // We can only recover one packet with an FEC packet.
674 if (packets_missing == 1) {
675 // Recovery possible.
676 std::unique_ptr<RecoveredPacket> recovered_packet(new RecoveredPacket());
677 recovered_packet->pkt = nullptr;
678 if (!RecoverPacket(**fec_packet_it, recovered_packet.get())) {
679 // Can't recover using this packet, drop it.
680 fec_packet_it = received_fec_packets_.erase(fec_packet_it);
681 continue;
682 }
683
684 auto* recovered_packet_ptr = recovered_packet.get();
685 // Add recovered packet to the list of recovered packets and update any
686 // FEC packets covering this packet with a pointer to the data.
687 // TODO(holmer): Consider replacing this with a binary search for the
688 // right position, and then just insert the new packet. Would get rid of
689 // the sort.
690 recovered_packets->push_back(std::move(recovered_packet));
691 recovered_packets->sort(SortablePacket::LessThan());
692 UpdateCoveringFecPackets(*recovered_packet_ptr);
693 DiscardOldRecoveredPackets(recovered_packets);
694 fec_packet_it = received_fec_packets_.erase(fec_packet_it);
695
696 // A packet has been recovered. We need to check the FEC list again, as
697 // this may allow additional packets to be recovered.
698 // Restart for first FEC packet.
699 fec_packet_it = received_fec_packets_.begin();
700 } else if (packets_missing == 0 ||
701 IsOldFecPacket(**fec_packet_it, recovered_packets)) {
702 // Either all protected packets arrived or have been recovered, or the FEC
703 // packet is old. We can discard this FEC packet.
704 fec_packet_it = received_fec_packets_.erase(fec_packet_it);
705 } else {
706 fec_packet_it++;
707 }
708 }
709}
710
711int ForwardErrorCorrection::NumCoveredPacketsMissing(
712 const ReceivedFecPacket& fec_packet) {
713 int packets_missing = 0;
714 for (const auto& protected_packet : fec_packet.protected_packets) {
715 if (protected_packet->pkt == nullptr) {
716 ++packets_missing;
717 if (packets_missing > 1) {
718 break; // We can't recover more than one packet.
719 }
720 }
721 }
722 return packets_missing;
723}
724
725void ForwardErrorCorrection::DiscardOldRecoveredPackets(
726 RecoveredPacketList* recovered_packets) {
727 const size_t max_media_packets = fec_header_reader_->MaxMediaPackets();
728 while (recovered_packets->size() > max_media_packets) {
729 recovered_packets->pop_front();
730 }
731 RTC_DCHECK_LE(recovered_packets->size(), max_media_packets);
732}
733
734bool ForwardErrorCorrection::IsOldFecPacket(
735 const ReceivedFecPacket& fec_packet,
736 const RecoveredPacketList* recovered_packets) {
737 if (recovered_packets->empty()) {
738 return false;
739 }
740
741 const uint16_t back_recovered_seq_num = recovered_packets->back()->seq_num;
742 const uint16_t last_protected_seq_num =
743 fec_packet.protected_packets.back()->seq_num;
744
745 // FEC packet is old if its last protected sequence number is much
746 // older than the latest protected sequence number received.
747 return (MinDiff(back_recovered_seq_num, last_protected_seq_num) >
748 kOldSequenceThreshold);
749}
750
751uint16_t ForwardErrorCorrection::ParseSequenceNumber(const uint8_t* packet) {
752 return (packet[2] << 8) + packet[3];
753}
754
755uint32_t ForwardErrorCorrection::ParseSsrc(const uint8_t* packet) {
756 return (packet[8] << 24) + (packet[9] << 16) + (packet[10] << 8) + packet[11];
757}
758
759void ForwardErrorCorrection::DecodeFec(const ReceivedPacket& received_packet,
760 RecoveredPacketList* recovered_packets) {
761 RTC_DCHECK(recovered_packets);
762
763 const size_t max_media_packets = fec_header_reader_->MaxMediaPackets();
764 if (recovered_packets->size() == max_media_packets) {
765 const RecoveredPacket* back_recovered_packet =
766 recovered_packets->back().get();
767
768 if (received_packet.ssrc == back_recovered_packet->ssrc) {
769 const unsigned int seq_num_diff =
770 MinDiff(received_packet.seq_num, back_recovered_packet->seq_num);
771 if (seq_num_diff > max_media_packets) {
772 // A big gap in sequence numbers. The old recovered packets
773 // are now useless, so it's safe to do a reset.
774 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Big gap in media/ULPFEC sequence numbers. No need "
775 "to keep the old packets in the FEC buffers, thus "
776 "resetting them.";
777 ResetState(recovered_packets);
778 }
779 }
780 }
781
782 InsertPacket(received_packet, recovered_packets);
783 AttemptRecovery(recovered_packets);
784}
785
786size_t ForwardErrorCorrection::MaxPacketOverhead() const {
787 return fec_header_writer_->MaxPacketOverhead();
788}
